<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>This submission looks particularly at the opportunities, pitfalls and lessons learned in organising collaborative procurement between local authorities as well as aspects of how local authorities manage procurement at a local level using Durham County Co</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Written submission from the North East Procurement Organisation (LPG 34)</span></p><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 18pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Executive Summary</span></h1><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This submission </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is from the North East Procurement Organisation (NEPO) which </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is the collaborative procurement hub for the 12 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">local </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">authorities in the North East</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. It </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">highlights the opportunities, pitfalls and lessons learned in organising collaborative procurement between local authorities </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">through a regional collaborative procurement approach </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">including aspects of how procurement is managed locally </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">quoting some relevant examples from Durham County Council</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The submission makes several recommendations gained </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">form</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the experience of NEPO and its members, focusing on skills; a strategy for what should be bought nationally/regionally/locally; how social care procurement should be supported; and more transparent ways of funding collaborative procurement.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 18pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Background to Procurement in Local Government in the NE</span></h1><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NEPO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> consists of 20</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> officers manag</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> contracts with spend of c£200m pa. The region spends c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">£2.5bn</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> per annum on goods and services</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Each LA has a procurement function and unique structure, status and strategy. NEPO was reformed and given a broader remit in 2010 to use category management across a wider range of categories and contracts. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NEPO is nearing completion of a regional framework for major construction projects to deliver a closer working relationship with major construction suppliers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, including local SMEs,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to improve quality</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, deliver</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> within budget, provid</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> apprenticeships</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">reduc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> environmental impacts. Construction makes up 15% of spend in the region. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Progress</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in social care</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (25% of spend)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> has been difficult and whilst  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NEPO now has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">contracts</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">/frameworks</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> for a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> social care</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">emarketplace</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, community equipment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and prepaid cards, areas such as residential care have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">proven</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> difficult </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">due to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the pressure already on provider margins, different </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">policies/</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">requirements</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> judicial reviews.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Integration with the NHS in the region may lead to future collaborative procurements for learning and disability care informed by the work done post Winterbourne and by Department of Health support for a regional market position statement which NEPO is coordinating.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NEPO has put in place a new process for managing residential homes for children and young people aimed at improving quality, reducing costs by attracting new entrants into the local market. A framework would have locked out new providers. The project involved substantial commitment by the regions commissioners and extensive engagement with providers, most of whom were not used to the new standards and processes involved.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">A recent Strategic Review of NEPO identified a number of significant changes in the local government procurement environment which will culminate in greater complexity; reduced activity and a tendency for increased fragmentation of spend on similar categories.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In this review it was reported that o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ne </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NE authorities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> addressable procurement spend f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">el</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">l from £79m in 2009/10 to £58m in 2013/14 (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">26.6% </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">reduction</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> through a combination of reduced settlement grants, putting local business first, partnership/outsourced contracts and other changes to the landscape. Spend will continue to reduce as the next spending round takes effect.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Other factors affecting the procurement landscape include:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ustaining the third sector as grants reduce</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">l</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">eisure trusts spinning off</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rading companies takings services out of LAs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">linical commissioning groups </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">/</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Wellbeing Boards</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">utsourcing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">/ </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">strategic partnerships </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">/ </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">joint ventures remove procurement responsibility from LAs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">DWP responsibilities transferred to LAs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ommunity right to challenge</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ocial value act</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">academies/</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">free schools moving out of scope for LAs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ublic health moving to LAs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Review recommended a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> more accountable governance structure </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">give the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NEPO </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">“hub” </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">clearer </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">direction and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">support.  A</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">new NE </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Regional Procurement Strategy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> informed by the NEPO Strategic Analysis System </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">(see later)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> will</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> determine </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">what is best procured at a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">national, regional and local </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">level.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendation 1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">: </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">vest in developing a better understanding of what works in procurement of social care and develop solutions for a rapidly changing policy landscape involving Health and LAs.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendation 2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> The sector needs a consistent strategy to identify at what level – local, regional, national – procurement and collaboration can be most effective.</span></li></ol><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 18pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Does Local government procurement deliver value for money and social value?</span></h1><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">LAs in the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NE</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> measure and report value for money differently which makes consistent reporting </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">problematic, however</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> procurement teams and NEPO have a good record in delivering savings in particular in commodity goods and services.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Durham has a focus on whole life value delivered through managing price, demand, payment terms, cost avoidance, cost reduction</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> process reengineering</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> negotiating rebates and developed a Social Value Task Force with key stakeholders.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NEPO Stakeholder Board</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, including</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> representatives from the NE Chamber of Commerce, the Federation of Small Business</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> third sector</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">created the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NEPO Business Club </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">n innovative</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> programme to train</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> local SME </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">bidders in tendering procedures and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">encourages </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">early engagement with supply markets to influence </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">strategy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> The Business Club events are run free of charge to suppliers and at no cost to the public purse.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Involvement of residents is carried out at a LA level rather than by NEPO. In Durham commissioning and procurement decisions are influenced by Area Action Partnerships (AAPs) and through a Citizens Panel established in 2009 with 2,500 residents consulted on council services such as waste recycling centres, a leisure </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">centre review, libraries and the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">councils</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> budget priorities which will include procurement options.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Durham AAP’s involve local people in spending decisions, identifying gaps in service provision and local organisations that could bridge them. AAP Board members take their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">v</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">fm</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> responsibilities seriously. Over the last </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">three</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> years AAP’s have been able to vote on the best use of local budgets of between £20k to £60k for the most needed local projects.  Many have panels to scrutinise proposals in detail and Boards have rejected proposals on the basis of duplication or </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">poor </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">value for money. This autumn  AAPs will each host an open forum to provide</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> further </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">input to the council</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s Medium Term Financial Planning including identify</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ing potential </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">savings</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NEPO supports LA programmes to engage with local suppliers such as Buy Durham, Buy Sunderland First and recent initiatives in South Tyneside, concentrating on </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">how supplier capability improvements</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">implementing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">“Quick Quotes” to help automate </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">/ make more transparent </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the procurement of smaller </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">value quotes/tenders </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for local businesses. NEPO </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Portal </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">also provides a module to help prime contractors </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">source</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> local</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> sub-contractors for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">supply chains.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">: Give LA procurement the recognition it deserves for meeting the challenge of delivering savings in a legally compliant way whilst supporting local economies.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 18pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Do LAs take sufficient advantage of collaborative procurement?</span></h1><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NE</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> LAs level of collaboration is good</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> but there</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> significant barriers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">no </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">mandat</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> - each </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">collaboration depends on individual commitment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">LAs committed to support</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> local suppliers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">different contract dates delay </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">take-up</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ultiple parties requiring </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">extensive stakeholder management;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NEPO attempted a Hub </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&amp;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Spoke model where a lead LA would conduct procurement for all members</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> on behalf of NEPO. This had limited success as LAs lack the capacity and priority to manage 11 partners </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">- </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">it has only worked where a new requirement means less rationalisation of requirements and where the lead has a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">priority </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">need for the contract itself</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tandardising specifications and processes for all</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> requires persistence and determination but can succeed, e.g. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">bringing six LA children’s services commissioning processes for residential homes together.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NEPO’s online procurement </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">P</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ortal provides a critical resource for collaboration. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It is u</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">sed by all LAs and NEPO to conduct </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">all p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rocurement </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">exercises </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">online</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> greatly appreciated by supplier</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> with easier access to more opportunities. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="22" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Collaborative procur</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ement often leads to framework</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> agreements which make no commitment to suppliers and requires LA’s to conduct mini-competitions</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> for their specific needs. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Frameworks make an individual LAs procurement process faster and easier with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">some</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> drawbacks:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">framework</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">may not</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> meet specific </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">local </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">needs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">or include local suppliers;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">locks new or improving suppliers out for the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> period of the framework;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s there is no commitment the suppliers are not generally encouraged to offer</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  best value for money and whilst LAs could join together there is no inherent route to aggregate demand for better terms;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">framework procurements are usually funded by a rebate on suppliers based on spend earned by the procuring organisation which may not be transparent to customers.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="23" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NEPO’s funding model involves both subscriptions from members and the retention of a proportion of rebate earned on spend through contracts which is fully transparent</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Because of our regional ownership there is generally more effective aggregation in our procurements and most rebate is retained and recycled back to members rather than transferring to other public sector buying organisations.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="24" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">An example of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">an innovative </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">solution</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> is the managed service “NEPRO” </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">created for the procurement of consultancy/professional services</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> by NEPO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. There is a continuing need to employ experts to deliver projects which LAs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">cannot do themselves</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. Many projects are relatively small and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">urgent so</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> a fully com</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">pliant EU procurement process c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ould be a barrier. Customers may not know who can best deliver their needs and suppliers complain that they frequently miss out on opportunities. NEPRO offers a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">managed service with a fast, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">comprehensive </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">legally compliant </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">approach</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. In the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NE</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> we are using NEPRO to identify the best local professional services </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">(</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">SMEs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, ensuring increased opportunities to improve the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ir business with the hope that they can access more </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NEPRO </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">customers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="25" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Central</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Government procurement</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s can be useful for local authorities when they </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">target</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> national markets, take account of the specific needs of the sector and are properly supported through implementation. A good example of this is the recent procurement by GPS with Pro5 of an Insurance framework which featured comprehensive and responsive engagement with local government so that it is now proving effective in delivering savings for the customers. NEPO is working with GPS and Pro5 to market and support the framework and take-up is looking </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">good for such a complex new area.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="26" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">There are other nationally procured frameworks which have proved much less effective </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">such as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ICT. This is often down to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">insufficient </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">understanding and consultation with local government customers and suppliers. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The sector also has a tendency to procure solutions for new requirements in a fragmented way and then struggle to retrospectively harness the buying power of the sector as whole. NEPO is helping through the national </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">emarketplace</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> framework and is working with the LGA to procure a collective switching deal for residents where local contracts are not yet widespread.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="27" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Energy procurement has been a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">longstanding </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">feature of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">public sector </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">collaboration. NEPO buys energy for the LAs in the region and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">shares information and experience </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">with GPS</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and Pro5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. NEPO believes that further aggregation; by having a single energy buyer for the public sector would </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">NOT</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> be a good idea. There are too few powerful suppliers and greater concentration would promote a monopoly. A single buyer would become more remote from end customers and reduce innovation (we have 8,000 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NE </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">customer locations including schools and leisure centres). </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="28" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">: A review should be commissioned on how best to fund procurement and public sector buying organisations in a more strategic and transparent way which may incentivise better collaboration.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 18pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">PFI</span></h1><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="29" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Durham</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> has used PFI </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">arrangements in a variety of circumstances. Building Schools for the Future delivered a successful partnership which has been able to meet educational objectives and provide value for money. It provides a flexible and responsive approach to overcome significant challenges which inevitably arose during the development process.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="30" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">One problem that is now being experienced with PFI is the difficulty of attempting to join up local service provision between LA and health PFI’s. The challenge of negotiating terms, costs and values is so arduous that the only outcome has been to agree co-location. The PFI financial investment arrangements need to be more flexible to meet the challenge of LAs and health working more integrated way.    </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-indent:3pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 18pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Does local government have the skills and expertise?</span></h1><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="31" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">After a period of expansion in the region’s procurement teams, units are now being merged and downsized and remain vulnerable both to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">cuts</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and the departure of experienced staff to other sectors</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">particularly t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Universities and Health. The NEPO </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">eview recommended </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">less</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> duplication of resources </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and more sharing of scarce </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">expert</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e. There is a clear shortage of experience in the procurement of social care where the need is perhaps greatest, but the timescales and effort required to deliver results means that it is a struggle to justify the priority required.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="32" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">One of NEPO’s roles in developing procurement capability regionally has been delivery </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">intensive training in category management </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> over</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> 200</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> staff. NEPO </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and LA </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">staff </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">are also supported </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in obtaining qualifications through the Chartered Institute of Purchasing and Supply.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="33" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">As LAs downsize, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NEPO is finding that the capacity to collaborate is getting harder especially where service area experts are needed to help specify requirements, support tender evaluations and implement changes to suppliers or processes.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="34" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendation 5:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> There should be a national approach to skills and developing/retaining procurement talent to help LAs continue to invest despite financial restrictions and this could usefully prioritise social care where the skill base is lowest.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Does local government have sufficient understanding of procurement expenditure and markets?</span></h1><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="35" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Building on previous experience </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> spend analysis work, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NEPO’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> new Strategic Analysis System that has been implemented across all </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">12</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> NE </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">uthorities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, supported by the LGA</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is an enabler, allowing each LA to interrogate their spend data down to transaction level detail. The information can be ‘sliced and diced’ in a wide number of ways depending on requirements, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e.g. to monitor</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> contract compliance, spend </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">by</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> supplier, by category, with SMEs, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">location o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">f suppliers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">A regional overview of all 12 LAs combined information is also available through NEPO.  By u</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">nders</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tanding the supply market is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">important for local authorities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> so the system</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> he</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">lps identify local SME’s and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">third sector organisations </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">support activity to improve the social, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">economic development of an area. It can also help to identify the proportion of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">authority spend with a supplier relating to its overall turnover across the region both to identify key suppliers and manage potential risks of over dependence.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="36" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The system include</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> other market intelligence feeds in one place. Regular uploading of data provides a near real time view of spend – a very powerful tool </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">inform the development of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rocurement strategies. Each LA system feed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> into a Regional System </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">providing an overview of spend which</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> support</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> collaboration</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and identifies suppliers on whom we are over dependent.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="37" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NEPO </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">uses a well established regional category management approach</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to make the procurement process </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">more strategic, including looking at the totality of spend using our data and a thorough analysis of supply markets.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="38" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">LAs in the region are all working on Market Position Statements for adult social care with the support of Department of Health</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, coordinated by NEPO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. These will set out for providers’ information on trends, supply </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">vs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> demand and the commissioning intentions of LAs to inform</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">investment decisions to the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">future </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">needs of social care</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> users</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="39" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendation 6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">: Effective procurement requires excellent data and analysis and begs for a more coordinated and intensive approach to improving the tools and experience in all regions. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 18pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">How well does local government manage procurement risk?</span></h1><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="40" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">upplier financial failure </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is one of the most common issues for procurement with</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the need </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for replacement supply and limiting</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">restrictions in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">competition.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="41" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NEPO has experienced three such instances and has been able to ensure supplies and find alternative suppliers. Future risks can be mitigated by carrying out thorough financial assessments in the tendering process. Each LA has different processes and standards </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">which is onerous for suppliers </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">but </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">increasingly a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">risk based approach </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is used to make the effort required consistent with the level of real risk</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> NEPO has been working with its LA members to harmonise documentation for several years.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="42" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NEPO contracts do not make commitments to suppliers on future level of spend. Contacts are designed to be as flexible as possible within the restrictions of the regulations and we work with suppliers to respond to changing circumstances.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="43" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Durham</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and NEPO apply Sustainable Procurement Policies including the use of sustainable timber and other social value considerations </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> tenders to assess and score risks and a supplier’s ability to mitigate them appropriately. The region is working on a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">new</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Flexible Framework to improv</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> sustainability and social value in our supply chains.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="44" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendation 7:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Each LA has its own policies and standards for managing risk in areas such as financial, insurance, health and safety, equality and diversity and recently social value. A clear policy direction would help achieve a better balance between local flexibility and more consistent standards for suppliers.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 18pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">What stops fraud and makes procurement accountable?</span></h1><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="45" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">LA procurement decisions are very visible to suppliers and the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">R</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">emedies Directive has encouraged a culture of challenge if there is any suggestion of a process not working fairly. This in turn tends to make procurement </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">more</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> risk averse.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="46" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The NEPO Portal provides a transparent audit trail with approvals required to proceed through the stages of procurement.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="47" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">LAs publish statutory procurement data and are publishing details of contracts let on the NEPO Portal</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="48" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">External audits each year review the control arrangements in place and internal audit will look at the likelihood and impact of a risk materialising in procurement</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">- particularly in achieving value for money - and target intensive testing where there isn’t strong enough evidence of effective controls.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="49" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Fraud and Anti-Corruption policies are</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> commonly in place</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">propriety of procurement is subject to strong internal control frameworks and by the scrutiny of elected members. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Durham</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> provides guidance and training to all staff on the prevention and detection of fraud and operates a confidential reporting and investigation process.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="50" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Each LA uses different systems to control the raising of orders and payment of invoices with approval processes and reporting in place to deter and identify causes for concern.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>